# {{.Name}} — AI Agent Context

## Goal
Minimal Go program that places an outbound call through the ClutchCall gateway.

## Runtime
- Endpoint: `{{.Endpoint}}` (override via `CLUTCHCALL_ENDPOINT`)
- Credentials JSON: `service_account.json` (override via `CLUTCHCALL_CREDENTIALS`)
- Native FFI: requires `libclutchcall_core_ffi.so` on the loader path.
  Build it from the SDK repo with `bazel build //core:clutchcall_core_ffi.so`
  and export `LD_LIBRARY_PATH=<sdk>/bazel-bin/core`.

## Editing Rules
- Do **not** hand-edit serde structs. The Go bindings in `github.com/clutchcall/sdk/go/pkg`
  are regenerated by `clutchcall/tools/apirpc_compiler/generate_bridges.py`. If you need a
  new RPC field, update the schema upstream and regenerate.
- After bumping the SDK pin, run `clutch migrate` from this project root to surface breaking
  schema changes.

## Common Tasks
- Add an inbound handler: see `client.AnswerIncomingCall` in the SDK.
- Bridge to an LLM: pattern from `clutchcall-sdk/go/examples/openai_agent`.
